<strong>WORKS CITED</strong>
<br><br>
Add a &#8216;Works Cited&#8217; entry at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br><br>
If the brochure is authored, include the name of the author at the start of the Works Cited entry followed by the title. If the author and publisher are the same, begin the entry with the title. 
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<em>Title</em>. Publisher, year of publication. 
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br><br>
Abbreviate <em>University</em> to <em>U</em>. For further information on common academic abbreviations, see 1.6.2 in the <a href="http://west-sydney-primo.hosted.exlibrisgroup.com/UWS-ALMA:default_scope:UWS-ALMA21186157620001571" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MLA Handbook (8th edition)</a>. 
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<span class="hover" title="Title"><em>Transport Access Guide: Penrith Campus</em></span>.
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Western Sydney U</span>,
	<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2009</span>.
</blockquote>
<br>
